This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it focuses on predicting personality from written text on social media. Additionally, the use of Word Embedding features suggests a natural language processing approach. 

The Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with social media data and aims to develop a model applicable to most users on Twitter. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is another possibility as the paper uses Gaussian Processes regression, a machine learning technique, to develop the personality prediction model. 

The Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with analyzing and predicting user behavior on social media. 

Finally, the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper does not explicitly deal with security or privacy concerns, but it does involve analyzing user data on a public social media platform.
